    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house in Toronto, is essentially a secure holding place for funds and documents until all the conditions of the sale are met. Think of it like a highly regulated, neutral third party—a professional, not just some random bank account—that holds the money and the title documents. It's crucial because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money doesn't go to the seller until the buyer has the deed, and the deed doesn't transfer until the money is confirmed. It keeps the whole transaction from devolving into a chaotic, messy scramble, which is exactly what you'd expect from a large, multi-faceted property deal.",
      "source": "target",
